titles.title: I Found a Husband When I Picked up the Male Lead

data.title: The Rewards of Marriage
title_synonyms: I Found a Husband When I Picked up the Male Lead
data.synopsis: Notorious for her extravagant spending, Wilhazelle Fossier drove her house to complete financial ruin. To pay her family's debt, she resolves to collect a bounty from the wealthy Duke Heillos by finding his missing nephew. Although her search is successful, until the skeptical duke can confirm the young boy's identity, Wilhazelle must spend one month living at the Heillos manor. But when one month turns into one year and a contract marriage, she starts to wonder if the money is worth it! (Source: Tapas Media)
data.background: The Rewards of Marriage has been published digitally in English by Tapas Media since June 12, 2022.

The Red Knight Seeks No Reward

data.title: The Red Knight Seeks No Reward
data.title_english: The Red Knight Seeks No Reward
title_synonyms: A Red Knight Does Not Blindly Follow Money
data.synopsis: Knee-deep in debt, Black Knight Judith's whole life revolved around money. She only bothered with actions that would net her a profit; no matter how unscrupulous the deed, it was fine as long as she was paid. However, after her superior stabs her in the back, she begins to rethink the tenets she has lived her life by. The next thing she knows, Judith has returned to the past, before she joined the Order of Black Knights. This time, she resolves to become a true knight—one who will not waver in the face of money and wields her sword with honor. The perfect opportunity to do so arrives when Captain Kaillou Lewalmeigh offers her a place in the Order of Red Knights. Abandoning her former cloak, Judith dons the red uniform, resolving to leave behind her money-grubbing habits and embrace the morals and righteousness of knighthood. [Written by MAL Rewrite]
data.background: The Red Knight Seeks No Reward has been published digitally in English by Tapas Media since January 19, 2022.

data.title: Sweet Regard
data.synopsis: Poor, miserable Kohei! His cherished little sister decides to run off and get married on the sly . . . and then a freak car accident takes her out of his life for good. As Kohei's heart struggles to mend in the wake of family tragedy, who should show up on his doorstep but his once-despised brother-in-law Shingo? Suddenly, Kohei's days and nights are ruled by torturous nightmares . . . and a strange, sweet longing. Will Kohei let Shingo see him at his most vulnerable, or will he keep his door locked forever? . . . . Thanks to a life marked by one tragedy after another, bitter Kohei is certain that he'll never know true love. However, his brother-in-law Shingo can't help but fall for the very man who despises him! In order to survive, these two men must admit to their secret wishes and face their deepest fears . . . together! (from June back cover)

title_synonyms: Give My Regards to Black Jack
data.synopsis: Saitou Eijirou is a newly established intern doctor, who is forced to take on a second night job at another, much smaller hospital because of the extremely low pay he receives. As he bounces between the two different hospitals, he is forced to dig deeper and deeper into Japan's largely corrupted medical society and starts to question even his own initial beliefs, as he asks himself just what being a doctor means. (Source: ANN)
data.background: In 2002, Black Jack ni Yoroshiku received Award of Excellence in manga category at the 6th Japan Media Arts Festival. Black Jack ni Yoroshiku was published digitally in English as Give My Regards To Black Jack by Digital Manga Guild from June 30 to August 15, 2013.
